The log collector intercepts console methods by replacing them on the global console object while preserving the originals:

const originalLog = console.log;
console.log = (...args: unknown[]) => {
  collector.capture('log', args);
  originalLog.apply(console, args);
};

For message formatting, convert each arg to string: if string, use as-is. If Error, use `err.message + err.stack`. Otherwise, try `JSON.stringify(arg)`, falling back to `String(arg)`. Join with spaces.

The background and offscreen scripts run in different JS contexts, so each gets its own LogCollector instance. The background script can retrieve offscreen logs by sending a message to the offscreen document. Add a new message type 'bg:getLogs' that the offscreen handler responds to with its log entries.

Files to create/edit: (1) Create platform/browser-extension/src/log-collector.ts, (2) Edit background.ts to initialize, (3) Edit offscreen/index.ts to initialize and handle bg:getLogs message.
